,Recommended,247080,24155314,"Posted: 7 July, 2016",all,Lapin,"-Insert obvious positive points on the graphic and soundtrack--Insert good recommendation for the majority that probably played this game and are looking for validation that the game is good--Insert remarks on how sloppy the structure of this review is and how it's painted in darkness-Ultimately, the question that matters most is:Is Crypt of the necrodancer enjoyable for me?As with all games, not everyone will enjoy this. In fact, even a rouge-like lover might not like this due to it's vastly different playstyle.The biggest turnoff that could ruin one's enjoyment is that the game islargely trial and error. There is almost zero chance of recovering from a mistake in a boss fight and this will end your run. While common in rougelikes, the bosses in this game are unforgiving. Any new enemy you encounter is and will (probably) kill you. It is nigh impossible to complete the gamewithout knowing how to deal with them.Fortunately, there is a practice dungeon that allows you to figure out how to deal with these obstacles.That said, (your experience) how frustrating this game gets depend whether or not you choose and have the patience to use this feature.Spend an hour or two practising against all mini-boss/bosses should you get this game. There are other minor qualms about the game but overall, it was a great experience and the design of certain enemies are ingenious.Note: There isa character (Bard)that would make the game mucheasierdue to the removal of time pressure imposed by the rhythms andchanges the game into a turn-based strategic onebutthe point above stands firm. Because this removes a core element of the game (the rhythimic pressure), it becomes just another rouge adventure and you will not be playing the same game that is advertised.The game itself is fairly short and is broken into four (4x4) zones and there is a notable difficulty spike in the latter zones.The approach to beating each level is vastly different.The upside? You are allowed to skip zones after beating them once.Zone 1 and 2 allows you to take things slow. -Kiting-Zone 3 forces you to manage and balance the different skill sets the enemies have and take the pre-emptive strike before you are swarmed. (Bad RNG can happen in this zone so be prepared for frustration.)Zone 4 requires fast planning and twitchy reflexes.-------------TL:DR-------------Shuffle and boogie to da beat like your bootie in da heat dancing cha-chain the crypt. And here we go! Forward backward rock-step, side together siderock-step~ConclusionGreat game, not for everyone. If you have twitchy reflexes, patience practising, like strategy (more so chess as opposed to RTS) and rouge-like games, this is the game foryou!Otherwise, grab the game on sale for a taste of this unique masochistic hybrid."
