,Recommended,247080,34003581,Posted: 3 August,all,Graham Crackers,"Indie Rogue-Likes are a dime a dozen on Steam these days, but Necrodancer stands out by being both creative and really, really fun to play.While it may not be the next Nuclear Throne in terms of depth, Necrodancer does have a few tricks up its sleeves to keep things interesting. A half dozen or so unlockable characters (all with their own unique twists and stipulations), a customizable item pool, and of course the traditional random level generation are here, but I often found the smaller things, like being able to dig through walls, more fun to mess around with. There's a lot of replay value as well, if you don't mind the challenge that is.And speaking of challenge, it can be a surprisingly difficult game at times. Although there's just 4 levels (with 3 stages each), you'll know the ins and outs of every one of them before long.But let's be real here. The soundtrack is an incredibly crucial part of any good rhythm game, and Necrodancer knocks its music out of the park. This isn't a game OST pretending to be a dance album, it IS a dance album. Hands down, this game has some of the best beats I've heard in a while.Everyone involved in this project has poured their heart and soul into it, and it really shows. If you like rhythm games, you absolutelyhaveto try this one!"
