,Not Recommended,247080,18021708,"Posted: 13 September, 2015",all,Fl3sh,"Just becuase your game is hard, doesn't mean it's good. Great concept here, total lack of content hidden behind frustrating layers of difficulty.Edit: To clarify since people seem to think I'm ""just doing it wrong"". I love a lot of the ideas in this game... a unique rhythm based dungeon crawler is right up my alley; but when you strip it all back what we have here is a shallow rougelike experience wrapped behind some incredibly charming art / style and a great soundtrack.There are 4 levels and a handful of enemy types, and no matter what the folks in the comments say you're going to die... a lot. The soundtrack is good, which is nice because you're going to be listening to the same 3 songs over and over as you attempt to master the enemy movements.I don't personally recommend it because I found the experience frustrating and unrewarding. Judging by the fact the current store shows the ratings as 98% positive I'm obviously the minority here. There are folks with hundreds of hours sunk into this game, so take my negative opinion with a grain of salt obviously."
