,Recommended,247080,12403114,"Posted: 7 October, 2014",all,theluigiguy,"tl;dr: Buy this game NOW if you enjoy dungeon-crawlers and/or roguelikes of any kind, innovation, and kickass music.At its core, Crypt of the NecroDancer is a rouge-like dungeon crawler. However, as you become more invested in the game's unique on-the-beat movement system, you'll begin to realize that NecroDancer is much more than that! Strategy comes into play when dealing with enemies with increasingly complex movement systems, especially when you get the urge to compete for a top spot on the speedrun and gold high school leaderboards in each Daily Challenge.DannyB's soundtrack for this game is fantastic and somehow hasn't gotten boring to me even after hours and hours playing the game. There are now 5 soundtracks to play with, and there's also always the option to enchant the Crypt with your own MP3s with ease!The story is surprisingly deep and well thought out - cutscenes are quick but pack a lot of meaning. They flesh out the lore of the NecroDancer very well, and offer a very satisfying resolution that ties up all loose ends.Brace Yourself Games handled Early Access like champs - there was and still is a huge amount of community involvement, and I've seen many community suggested features be implemented!Crypt of the NecroDancer WELL WELL WELL worth the cost. Buy it NOW if you have any interest! It's easy to pick up, but hard to master!P.S.: for any musicians out there, I can say that this game has definitely improved my rhythm-keeping skills!P.S.S.: In reference to my hours played: it's ok."
