76561197982302105,Recommended,247080,33502019,Posted: 13 July,all,monkey,"So I kept seeing this game and wondering why people liked it. Just watching the video and looking at the pics didn't quite convey the fun of the game. I thought I'd give it a try since it was on sale for $2.99. Well f#$# me I couldn't stop playing the damn thing. Highly addictive. The rhythm thing really adds a whole new challenge to the game. It's a lot trickier than it looks. It's not just some dumb mindless moving to a beat, you really have to choose your movements very carefully and strategically, all while keeping time with the beat. I saw one negative review and the person said they are a ""musician"" and they knew for a fact that the rhythm was not correctly synched or something like that. Well, I'm also a musician of 27 years, have a degree in music and teach people music for a living, and I can tell you the other reviewer is wrong, there is nothing wrong with the rhythm synchronization. I just played for like 3 hours straight and only missed a couple beats because of mistakes on my part. I had no problem synchronizing to the beat for almost a continuous 20-30 mins for each run that I did. When you first play the game it goes through this synchronization process, if you do that right you should have no problems with the rhythm synch."
