,Recommended,247080,11555489,"Posted: 4 August, 2014",all,SilverMike,"NecroDancer is a great rhythm-based Rogue-like where you take turns to the beat of the music.  Miss a beat, everything around you takes a turn anyway.  At first it sounds weird to not have all the time in the world to plan a move in an RL, but NecroDancer makes it work with basic patterns to all creatures.  The main challenge is balancing keeping the beat up with putting yourself in a good position to deal with whatever comes at you.  You need either quick decision-making or good muscle memory from repeated plays to deal with complex situations.Unreservedly recommend it once the game is completed.  $15 for early access is alright, but you'll probably have to be interested in the concept beforehand to feel fully happy about your $15."
,Recommended,247080,32836896,Posted: 26 June,all,daughtermurder™,"Before playing this game the last time I had really enjoyed a rhythm game was the original Audiosurf, released years ago. Prior to that, I'd fallen in love with and 100%'d Donkey Kong Jungle Beat for the Gamecube.If you enjoy games that involve rhythmic controls and emphasis on music you will appreciate this game. If you enjoy the challenge and gameplay of rogue-like games, in addition to the prior, you will love this game.It feels like The Binding of Isaac and DK Jungle Beat merged together and added a slight turn-based element to their gameplay (of course since the 'turns' are really just the beats of the music, you don't get the sort of planned engagements you would in a game like XCom in spite of the isometric view and grid-locked movement.I was skeptical before trying, but this is more than worth the $3 sale price it is selling for right now. I will probably buy the expansion DLC  before the summer sale is over."
,Recommended,247080,15735364,"Posted: 7 May, 2015",all,Gweebis,"Now that the full release of this game has been out for awhile, I feel compelled to write a review of this game.Crypt of the NecroDancer is a rogue like, rhythm based dungeon crawler that offers a unique challenge and experience, complete with multiple characters that have their own playing style that affects the gameplay greatly.Pros:- Probably the most important aspect of a rhythm game is its music. Crypt does not disappoint in the slightest with its amazing tunes, composed by the one and only Danny Baranowsky as well as awesome remixes by FamilyJules7x and A_Rival.- You can use your own music in the game, and this feature is implemented well.- The game provides a hard but fair style of gameplay, something that is sure to keep people doing runs over and over again.- Each of the characters adds an interesting twist (such as moving in cut time or being able to only use bombs) that provide an additional challenge for players to overcome.- This game has high replayability as no two runs are exactly the same.- A mix of items provides players with multiple ways to beatdown enemies to the beat.- The devs constantly provide updates and work hard to fix any bugs that people encounter along the way.Cons:- It can take awhile to get used to. You're probably not going to be able to get through Zone 1 on your first try. For some people, this may be a turnoff, though, if you're willing to put in the effort, you can really get a lot of enjoyment out of completing a run.- If you're trying to 100% this game... think again. One of the achievements may be impossible to get, which may turn some people away.- Pausing the game and regaining your pace can be rather difficult. While this may not sound like a big deal at first glance, there are some characters who will die if you miss a beat (Aria and Coda).Some people may complain about the price, but you can find some 33% off coupons floating around on Steam. It's not much, but 10 bucks is less than 15.TL;DR:If you like rogue likes, rhythm games, or dungeon crawlers, get this game. This game is an astounding combination of the three that works harmoniously. If the price seems like too much, go get a coupon from groups like Coupon Dumpster and that."
