,Recommended,247080,31283380,Posted: 21 April,all,freen,"In the Crypt of the NecroDancer you have to move with the beat to keep up your multiplier you get after killing monsters. Even though it doesn't look like it, this game offers so much i was truly shocked. The story isn't the driving factor here, it is the stellar gameplay which makes it so appealing.There are four main stages which gradually increase in difficulty while also introducing unique new monsters into the mix. The levels are all randomly generated (except the daily challenges which are the same for everyone). The gameplay controlled by your arrow keys is the most challenging game that i have played to this day and i still have a long way ahead of myself.I can wholeheartedly recommend this game to anyone looking for a game which they can pump a lot of hours into while being faced by great challenge, as the different characters introduce different handycaps and advantages."
