,Recommended,247080,16372183,"Posted: 13 June, 2015",all,pruwyben,"A great combination of a roguelike and a rhythm game. It borrows elements from games like Speluny and Binding of Isaac - permanent item/character unlocks, a daily challenge, and of course random level generation and permadeath. The rhythm aspect makes it unique - unlike most rhythm games, you don't have to hit a particular button at a particular time, but there is a lot of strategy in getting the timing right to kill enemies and avoid damage - strategy which is enriched by the variety of enemy move/attack patterns and a number of items that affect your own movement and attack. It's all about planning ahead, and thinking fast so you don't lose the beat."
