,Recommended,247080,11577505,"Posted: 6 August, 2014",all,Orange Freeze,"Crypt of the NecroDancer is exactly what it is described as: a rogue-like rhythm game.This game is all about patterns. Each type of enemy moves to the beat in a specific way, and you need to learn these patterns to effectively defeat them.The simplistic controls are what really drive this game home. You only use four buttons to perform all of the moves in the game - up, down, left, and right, to be precise. The game's control scheme is so simple, in fact, that you can play it with a USB-enabled dance pad, like the kind used for DDR-esque games. Personally I have not tried this, though I definitely want to!Even though this game is in alpha, it is still jam-packed with features to entertain you for hours of playtime. I highly recommend this game."
