,Recommended,247080,21057310,"Posted: 8 February, 2016",all,OregoX,"Crypt of the NecroDancerA little pixel Game I saw on a friends PC. I was a bit suspicious about that, but now I really like it.GamePlay:You control a little man/woman, depending on who you play. The only keys you have to press are ↑ , ↓ , → , ←.Sounds simple and not very exciting, but the most interesting part is, that you have to press them in the right rythm.^^Listen to the music in the background may helps.This is still not all. Every Enemy in the game also moves in this rythm and they have some patterns.(e.g Blue Slime: Moves one block up, skips a beat and then moves one block down.)This is one of the simplest patterns. Others have patterns with no set directions and they'll try to get you.Additional to that enemies may have some special attacks. (e. g Red Dragon: when you are in the same horizontal line the dragon will spit fire that deals damage to the entire horizontal line.)Items also exist which helps you to fight against enemies.Not to forget, other characters, other kinds of this gameplay. ;)Sometimes it's very challanging, even with the ""Bard"", where you have no rythm and the enemies move after you. Simple amazing idea!★ ★ ★ ★ ★Graphics:This is the part where I want to remove a Point. It is a PixelGame (and I like it), but I think it could be better. So just★ ★ ★ ★ ☆Story:Ähh... Well, even you may miss the story, because you try to finish the first floor 100 Times, I think it was something about saving someone... No Rating for no Knowledge.^^Music:I always love to make that catigorie, because I just use it in 2 different cases: Good Music or Horrible Music and I think you would guess correctly that this Music-based Game has a nice soundtrack.Even the Shopkeeper sings. :D★ ★ ★ ★ ★Worlddesign:It has a simple block design as simply as you can make Maps on your own. Not really special. The different types of Levels makes it not so repetitive, but I won't make any rate about this.Just saw i