,Recommended,247080,20185586,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,Jpdaniel,"I'm not a huge fan of turn-based games, the careful calculation isn't my cup of tea outside a bit of casual play. I like action roguelikes, which give me a challenge I can quickly work through, but by nature there'll always be a glut of deaths that seem more random chance than my fault.This game solves both problems. By making it technically turn-based but setting each turn to a less-than-half-second timer, every move is forseeable in advance; but you have to keep moving. So it beats me up but every time it does I realize I ""obviously"" could have just used that bomb, or staggered one more turn.Beating the final story is simply one of the most satisfying thing I've done because I felt like I had legitimately EARNED that victory through-and-through. Quick-thinking, experience, and timing got me there, not just lucky drops. That feeling is what makes this easily one of my favorite games I've ever played. But getting your face stomped in repeatedly in hopes of one day achieving the goal isn't for everyone. I'm just in the right place for this game.Also, good job on making the music bearable even after hearing it for 28+ hours"
