,Recommended,247080,15508908,"Posted: 23 April, 2015",all,Garlyle Wilds,"No joke, this was one of my favourite games of 2014.In theory, this is a really simple game.  Grid-based roguelikes have been done before.  The real seller of Crypt, however, is the impact of the game being set to music and moving rhythmically.Unlike a lot of similar games, Cryptforcesyou to learn and memorize patterns and react fast and skillfully, instead of spending forever mulling through cluttered inventories for the exact item to get you out of your situation.  It's about speed, snap decisions, and learning, and above all is completely fair -everythingin the game could be handledflawlesslywith just your starting equipment.There's a lot of other aspects that are strengths to it.  Mechanically, the game reaches an incredible level of play diversity, not just from the vastly different playable characters.  It also comes from the fact the massive pool of items arerarelyjust a straight upgrade over one another, and instead have different strengths, weaknesses, and benefits.  Presentation wise the game's super slick, charmingly animated, and the music is bloody amazing too.Do the thing.  Get the game.  It's amazing."
