,Recommended,247080,13158719,"Posted: 30 November, 2014",all,Karunamon,"Another day, another roguelike. This one has a very unique and downright fun mechanic - move to the music! Every move you make, every attack you make, needs to be on time with the (very well done, and very enjoyable) background track. Stay on beat and get more money to buy upgrades, miss beats, get attacked and probably get dead.Watch the intro video for a quick idea of how this works.Gamewise, this is your average roguelike dungeon crawler. It is fun, and the music mechanic is enough to carry the game through its few shortfalls, Bear in mind that this is early access and there is a decent amount of missing content. Many upgrades are not available, and one entire dungeon did not exist at time of writing.Recommend steering clear of the the ""add your own music"" feature, because frankly, it's crap. Beats continuing through silence, they're not detected accurately, and so on. The pack-in tracks are good enough that you won't want to do this anyways.That said, those minor issues aside, I really recommend this game in spite of the unfinished-ness. If this game is this good at this stage in its development, really, it can only get better. Thumbs up!"
