76561198090026955,Recommended,247080,11560556,"Posted: 5 August, 2014",all,KingDingo3,"As i am writing this please keep in mind this is from the early alpha build so there may be many things yet to be added into the game in the near future.This game is a really good mix of rhythm meets rouge-like rpg, when you begin you have little on you and can only move when the beat hits the sweet spot (or something like that), and as you go deeper into the Crypt, or zones (whatever you prefer), you will meet stronger monsters and newer upgrades, all of which have a unique take of gameplay. Please also note that you will die a few times on your first try but thats ok, when you die you have a chance to spend any gathered diamonds on upgrades or extra items found in chests and then try again. The Crypts/zones are always randomised meaning not every run will be the same, some will be easy as in the exit is right in front of you, other times you would need to fight through a mini-army to exit the place and will bring many challenges for you to face. At the end of each Crypt/zone, ussually on the forth floor, you will face one of three bosses, all of which brings an interesting take to battle.And if you get board with the in-game soundtrack (no idea why since the merchants singing is quite fun) you can always add your own music and try get through with your own beats.So far the alpha has three Crypts/zones with the forth in the making still, but what i've seen the game is really good and i would recommend this game to anyone for how fun its turned out to be.Personally i give this game a 9/10 (c^_^c)"
