,Recommended,247080,29380930,Posted: 20 January,all,Finolum,"Oh my god, this game... This game is as amazing as it may be hard.First of all, you CANNOT play this game if you aren't able to passively tap the beat of a song while thinking about something else at the same time, this is NECESSARY to the gameplay. It makes this game a turn based dungeon crawler where every turn lets you think for less than a second. If you miss a beat, you skip a turn.So there's what this is about : you play as Cadence, your everyday dungeon hero in a rogelike game where when you die, you'll have to restart BUT, at first the game introduces you to everything it has, starting by each zone in the game one after another, and then unlocking different characters with different gameplay mechanics, in order to keep the experience fresh.In the first like 20 hours, you'll learn how to beat the game in every zone with every character. And then you will start trying to complete the full dungeon in a row with any character you'd have chosen.Now, not only does this require a lot of time to reach (like, a LOT), but it also is kinda hard.For I love hardcore games as much as I love RPGs, the positive point was it could keep me busy for a large amount of time, but this aspect can also scare casual gamers.If you want to look for yourself, you'll see that beating the full game even with the easiest character has been done by 2% of the players, so the challenge is real, but it makes every achievement you get a real pride.Buy it."
