,Recommended,247080,33125024,Posted: 2 July,all,Bolzen,"If you're looking for a game with an well excecuted control gimmick, high skill ceilings, appealing simple aesthetic and a groove to go with it, Crypt of the NecroDancer may just be for you.Not only that, you've got covers of Danny B's amazing original soundtrack for the game by various artists, such as the Aria's Awakening by FamilyJulez, a metal remix of the entire OST or the synthwave covers by Sister Records.It also comes with a level editor, letting you experiment and get creative with the mechanics of the game and to top it all off, it's easily moddable, with a fully functioning Steam Workshop page that supports both custom levels and mods made by the community.The only true downsides to this game are it's lackluster story that, while it gives context to the gameplay, doesn't give a depth of lore that, let's be honest, a game like this doesn't need. The second true downside is it's, of course, the signature difficulty curves that comes with many Rouge-lites, though it's multiplied here as one has to memorize enemy patterns, terrain effects, weapon patterns and so much more.So, if you're ready to dedicate time to learn the ins and outs of this game, give it a go."
