,Recommended,247080,24727834,"Posted: 5 August, 2016",all,Penaz,"If I had to describe this game with one word, it would be ""Addicting"".The music, the graphics, the combat system, everything is addicting.But let's go in order, shall we?The musicDanny Baranowsky did an amazing work with the soundtrack, and that's an understatement. Just to make you understand: In over 8 years of gaming on Steam I've never even thought of buying a game's soundtrack, no matter how awesome it is.This time I did. And I'll probably buy it too, when the chance comes up.The tracks are energizing and the beats are well recognizable, which lets you concentrate on the game itself instead of the ""beat bar"" and adds that boost of energy that makes this game what it is.The graphicsSimple and colorful pixel art waits you in this game.The graphics change from zone to zone, while keeping consistency in the 4 levels of each zone, plus a special boss level that changes every time you play.The graphics themselves are not messy at all, but if there are many enemies on screen it could get quite difficult to concentrate on the rhythm enough to not lose track of a trap. But that's part of the game.The GameplayOooooooh the juicy part.The gameplay is innovative, a great mix of dungeon crawling, rhythm game, strategy, action and adventure.Each level is randomly generated and gives the player a new experience every time. Diamonds allow you to unlock new weapons and abilities and the whole gameplay system gives the impression of getting better and better even if you're stuck in a certain level or zone.The gameplay is relentlessly difficult, a single wrong move could ruin a whole great run, and you have really little time (usually one beat) to decide the next move. Even though it's difficult, the game is not unfair, it's just hard enough to make you keep trying harder and harder, to the point that you get worse instead of getting better (I'm talking from personal experience).The game has unlockable characters, each one with its own way of playing, which gives the game a whole lot of replayability; additionally there's the mod support which extends the game life a little more.The negativesIf I had to say something negative about the game, it would be the first loading screen, before accessing the lobby.On my system, playing the game means waiting at least 1 or 2 minutes at the loading screen, but the catchy tune that accompanies the loading makes everything better.Instead the other loads are instant, which makes replaying or changing mode a breeze.TL;DRIf you like hard games, great enegizing music and randomly generated maps. Get this game now.I got this game in a stretch of madness for buying something on Steam.I'm glad I did."
