,Recommended,247080,23048030,"Posted: 17 May, 2016",all,crumbs,"Honestly, I'm not a huge fan of roguelikes... I never seemed to grasp the concept of ""good"" or ""bad"" items, and I found the everchanging map layouts kinda disorienting.When I picked this game up, I expected the same cookie-cutter gameplay style. I'm very glad I was proven wrong.CotN is a fast-paced and quick-witted game based around completing actions based on the beat of the music playing in the background, and I found it quite amazing. It has a ton of replay value, it keeps you on edge and requires split-second reactions. Also, the music is really f*ckin' good.Maybe I'm biased, maybe I'm not. It's up to you if you wanna pick this game up for yourself. No regrets."
76561198025420270,Recommended,247080,15868189,"Posted: 17 May, 2015",all,me_dandrea,"Rythm-based roguelike dungeon crawler, where you have to press buttons to the beat of the music to move each turn.Putting aside the rythm gimmick, the game plays like a simple grid-based dungeon crawler. As you slay monsters and descend through the crypt, you find a variety of equipable items that upgrade your character. Enemy attacks come in predictable patterns which can be dodged, and your attacks likewise hit with different patterns depending on what weapon you use. The tactics aren't complicated, but it's easy to slip up when you're tasked with making several moves per second. The combination of speed, timing, and strategy is unique and feels very satisfying once you get the hang of it.The story, told through cutscenes, is unremarkable but not bad. Furthermore, the voice acting and pixel art are good, and the music is stellar. The game's focus is on its mechanics, but it manages to cobble together a compelling atmosphere as well.Playing each of the game's four zones one by one is relatively easy and allows you to buy upgrades between runs, but the marathon ""all zones mode"" is much more challenging. There are also several playable characters, each with their own mechanics, as well as local co-op multiplayer.A hugely successful experiment - lots of fun."
,Recommended,247080,33590920,Posted: 16 July,all,neko lewds,good stuff
,Recommended,247080,34471956,Posted: 24 August,all,Buff Orpington,"Fantastic roguelike-with-a-twist once you get over the initial hump of understanding the mechanics and unlocking a few new items. It's nice and difficult like a roguelike should be, and no one item can make you overpowered so there's not much point in resetting for certain drops. Lots of characters to choose from, lots of item combinations to discover, and lots of unlockables mean the replayability is high too, even for a roguelike."
