76561198004565666,Recommended,247080,12362970,"Posted: 4 October, 2014",all,brickey.8,"This game is a completely seamless mix of three rather disparate genres--roguelike, puzzle and rhythm game. All three enhance each other well. The rhythm component forces you to think on your toes despite the turn-based nature of the combat (which is really more of a fast-paced puzzle game than anything else, since it's always possible to defeat all foes without a scratch if you make the right moves). And the roguelike nature keeps it fresh, ensuring that the more exotic items and weapons are treats.The variety of characters, not to mention items and weapons, do a good job adding replay value. Some characters are way more difficult than others on purpose, but that just stretches out the fun longer.Item balance is among the best I've ever seen in a semi-roguelike--most of the better weapons are mixed blessings, the different rings and helmets are all equally useful in different ways, and item prices for the better items are well-tuned to present tough choices in shops (even if the choice is ""is it worth killing the shopkeeper""). You'll get runs with good luck and bad luck, but rarely will you have runs where the whims of the RNG are what made you lose or win--your power level is much more consistent than, say, Isaac or Spelunky. Plus even the best items are useless without skill, and with skill you can win with a basic dagger.Oh, and it has three phenomenal soundtracks. Not just one, three. And some extremely creative bosses.Overall, I heartily recommend this game for just about anyone. If you watch the trailer and think that could even potentially be fun for you, I guarantee it will be."
