,Recommended,247080,22465788,"Posted: 16 April, 2016",all,fawkineh,"This game is so very awesome. Words can't even describe the amount of happiness this little title has given me. I think what I love the most is you can play this game one handed as you sit back and relax in your comfy reclining chair. It's definitely a challenging title, but not in a way that makes you think the game is an ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥, but rather usually a death is the result of a screw up from you, the player. It makes you question your own stupidity or lack of attention that sets you in a rage against yourself, rather than against the game.The music is perfect. Zone 2 is my least favorite of the bunch, but there's so many classic tracks during the gameplay - Tracks like King Conga and 3-2 or even 4-3 are just utter perfection. Danny B deserves more acclaim from this work than he's already received. A rhythm game needs good catchy music, and Necrodancer has that in spades.The daily challenges offer a chance to separate the good players from the players like me. It's a nice touch, offering every player the game challenge, so you and some friends can compete against each other. There's a nice variety of items and shrines you can use to build your necrodancer with. A rougelike with a twist!I wouldn't recommend this game if you're deaf... or blind. I mean, that should be a given. But if you have one good hand and you like bouncing to the beat of some catchy music, you should purchase this title. And then buy yourself a t-shirt and continue gushing about your praise over this game to your girlfriend unitl she asks you to leave her alone. I mean, that's what I did. It worked out for me."
