,Recommended,247080,15546808,"Posted: 25 April, 2015",all,ShadowMario64,"With a lack of rhythm games in general, Crypt of the NecroDancer (or CotN) delivers with Grand Results. The controls only use the Arrow Keys, but it uses this limitation to its advanatge since some item can only be activated via 2 button press and forces you to not mess up, or it i'll cost you a heart or 2. Yes, it IS a simple rouge-like, but the game requires you to plan ahead, know the patterns of enemies, know what items do what, Etc. There are upgrades to the game, but it still requries the skill you had without said upgrade. the Co-Op mode feels weird with player 2 using WASD, but It still manages to work. The Game also offers different characters with differnet play styles, an online leaderboard via Daily Challenge, and Mod Support (lets hope we dont have to pay for these any time soon) The game gets VERY challenging after world 3, granted there are only 4 Worlds, and after beating the random boss at the end, you get a little cut-scene talking about the story of the game. Overall, this game can be enjoyed by most, if not all fans of Rouge-likes and Rhythm games, I give Crypt of the Necrodancer:9.8/10BUY IT, AND ENJOY IT (the 0.2 that isnt included is just some personal issuses)"
