76561198255233637,Recommended,247080,29669331,Posted: 3 February,all,Eugen,"extremely addicted to this game now.Amazing ost (with badass remixes) and hard gameplay, some story, game mods and workshop with level editor. Is there anything else that perfect dungeon-crawler might need?\Pixie kicked my butt hard.\"
,Recommended,247080,29947298,Posted: 15 February,all,Ebony,"Im in love with this game; I can't get enough. The gameplay is fun and wondering how your next run is going to go is always exciting. (like a lot of dungeon crawlers) What NecroDancer does differently than other dungeon crawler games is there isnt any real artifical difficulty. Everything is choreographed (except those darn bats) and it never feels like you were cheated out of run; you lost because -you- messed up. (or your hand cramped trying to do Bolt Death Metal)I can't forget of all things the music. With a great composer such a Danny Baranowsky and currently five other styles by other artists, you can guarentee at least seven or eight songs getting stuck in your head.All in all, this game has been a great experience and I look forward to see what else is in store for this masterpiece."
