,Recommended,247080,29702191,Posted: 4 February,all,vult boi,"I. Love. This. Game!(Even though I suck at it.)When I started playing this game, and I couldn't beat the first stage, I wasn't really good at catching rhythm in songs. But now, it's a piece of cake! You can really learn from this game. Anyone who is making music should try it out, to test their rhythm skills, and maybe learn how to play rogue-like dungeon games :PIt has a total of 10 different characters (and another one in the DLC), each having different playstyles than the others.The soundtrack is amazing! It's made by Danny Baranowsky. It features 24 tracks in the base, and 5 extra in the DLC! (on 4th of February 2017, I don't know if Dan will make more soundtrack (which I would really like, it's amazing))Not to mention, there are a couple remixes in the game too!-an EDM remix by A_Rival;-a metal remix by FamilyJules7x;-a freestyle retro remix by Jake 'Virt' Kaufman;-a synthwave remix by Girlfriend Records;-a (i don't know what music type it is) remix by OverClocked;-and a chiptune remix by Chipzel, featured in the Xbox One version!You can also upload your own tracks, and this game will even find the rhythm!The only problem I have with this game, it's really hard. You have to stay concentrated, feel the rhythm, know the patterns and think fast - I often find myself dying from little mistakes, but that's the process of learning, right?I recommend it for everyone. It's worth it, and I love it. You might rage a bit, miss a couple beats and die, but don't all games do that? If you like challenges, this game is for you! But I don't get it, why people say it's not a game for casual players. Who really cares? It's an amazing game! I found myself enjoying it all the time. GET IT!Have fun, and don't forget you have a shovel :necroshovel:"
