,Recommended,247080,11495790,"Posted: 31 July, 2014",all,pikkukalsari,"Crypt of the NecroDancer is a rhytm based dungeon crawler with some roguelike elements and great tunes.CotN is a turn based game where every beat serves as a turn. This means that if you miss a beat you miss a turn. You basically need just 4 buttons to play the game: left, right, up and down. These are used also in combination to use items and spells by pressing up+left to eat an apple i.e. though you can assign a single button for these functions also.You find consumables from the levels to heal yourself, spells like fireball or freeze and different weapons and armors. There are also diamonds that serves as a currency in the games hub where you can purchase persistent additions to your adventuring. Besides additional health the rest of the upgrades are added to the map generation for you to find.Enemies are varied as in how often they move (in beats) and in which patterns (up and down, following you etc.) and bosses are tougher and more damage dealing creatures of course.What makes CotN different is the rhytm-system. Roguelike-type-of-games are usually hard already but NecroDancer makes you do important decisions on the fly and likes to punish the player for hesitating. If you thought Spelunky was hard you've seen nothing (this is a warning). You have to study the movements patterns of the enemies and find the right timing and way to deal with each enemy. This changes with your gear since some weapons allow you to attack diagonally and you have to consider the right timing to launch that spell you've been saving.Pros:-Music, music, MUSIC.-Fast paced, quick runs-Graphics are lovely-Challenging-Different game modes and co-opCons:-I didn't like the color effect that you get when coin multiplier gets higher,makes the game look messy particularly in the second zone.-Not sure if the music/movement calibration is the most accurate possible solution-If the beat calibration is of it's pretty much impossible to play the hardcore mode-Could have more items that alter the gameplayVery good distraction for coffee break gaming and for the laughs with friends.I felt that the price was a bit high for the game but not for the soundtrack - and thisdoesn't mean that the game is bad - just that Danny B makes some badass tunes."
