76561198042801239,Recommended,247080,16742146,"Posted: 27 June, 2015",all,CritHam,"Crypt of the NecroDancer. So what is it? It is a dungeon crawler where turns are taking place in a certain (dictated by song) rhytm.Basically you go on andventure of 4 zones, each having 4 levels. Design of each zone is unique and entertaining, each with different enemies traps and hazards. At end of each level you will meet a Miniboss (7 different types, which most have upraged version of itself), and at the end of each level you will meet a boss (4 types).When you finish a ""run"" (beat 4 zones in a row) you will meet final boss. But if you are able to defeat him it's not over. After it you will have 2 more characters that push story to play with. ""What story?"" Every time you beat any zone with a character you will get a cutscene (don't worry you can skip it).""But why did you say 2 more charactersthat push story?"" Because you will have 6 differeant characters that do not push story and are there to make this game even longer!Gameplay feels slick and nice with amazing songs (3 differeant song packs {normal, kind-of-disco and metal one} + a beat analizer so you can adapt your own songs to the game).  Game is quite well balanced and only issue that i have is bosses at end of zones are too easy (excluding ""main"" ones). Local Co-Op is sweet, game has controller support and achievment system.What could i say more?10/10"
