,Recommended,247080,15614636,"Posted: 29 April, 2015",all,Ash,"I've been playing this game a lot again lately and i've changed my mind. I'm gonna copy some of my old review in this. (The old review was done when I was called ""Hostile Elder Oak"")Crypt of the Necrodancer is an amazing game. You just gotta play it a lot to understand.Yeah, I DID edit the files to unlock the level editor but i'm not skilled enough to beat the game. *gasp*It's a unique game. When was the last time you saw a rhythm based dungeon crawler? The closest thing I can think of is ""Patapon"" for the PSP but it's not a dungeon crawler or top-down. Look it up.You can even put in your own .mp3 or .ogg files for the music. There's a lot of different playable characters, 4 different dungeon types, a level editor, a load of items, lots of enemies, etc.You can even add your own music (and play to the beat of the song).One bad thing is that it's random so you could find a really cool weapon in one run, nothing good in another.Apart from that, I DO recommend this game.That's if you can play it...---------------------------------------------ORIGINAL (negative) REVIEW:---------------------------------------------As much as I enjoy this game (sometimes), I can't recommend it, unless you like overly hard, unforgiving games, then go ahead.I'll start with the good things.It's a unique game. When was the last time you saw a rhythm based dungeon crawler? The closest thing I can think of is ""Patapon"" for the PSP but it's not a dungeon crawler or top-down. Look it up.You can even put in your own .mp3 or .ogg files for the music. There's a lot of different playable characters, 4 different dungeon types, a level editor, a load of items, lots of enemies, etc.Now the bad things.Just like Magicite or The Binding of Isaac, The game is pretty much based on luck. Roll a 6 and you win. Roll any other number, you lose. You need to be good at enemy pattern remembrance, have a good eye, be good with music and hope you get good items. Most of the game for me consisted of getting far and then dying some sort of cheap death you couldn't avoid, which isn't fun. It doesn't help that some enemies move randomly. Zone 4 didn't even feel like part of the game.When I said about the load of playable characters, most of them I have are useless.The Monk can get any shop item for free but dies instantly by touching gold, which is a lot harder than it sounds.The Dove (I think) Can't attack. Come on, really?And the level editor? You have to beat the game. Do you really think I would do that?So, should you get it?I would say no. Even if you really want it, I thought the same thing.I'm not saying that the game is badly made or anything. It's actually really well made."
76561198059619193,Recommended,247080,15574209,"Posted: 26 April, 2015",all,It'sPresidentTobias,"I bought this game out of pure and utter intrest. Rhythm games aren't really my thing, but a rhythm dugeon crawler? I only wanted to see for myself how they pulled it off. The fact that there are negative reviews for this game boggles my mind. The combat is not repetative, the negative reviews say it is. True, the enemy's do follow patterns, but the combinations of enemies and traps in each room makes you think of new ways to use these patterns, while the rhythm aspect makes sure you can't think for long. The soundtrack is absolutely stellar, however personally I prefer the EDM remix. In short, an amazing, beutiful and creative game that could only have sprung from the mind of a genius. 11/10-Will buy a dancepad to play."
