,Recommended,247080,29968295,Posted: 16 February,all,mata,"So this is my 2nd review for this game, right after completing the first half of the story (all zones once) there might be a little bit of spoilers here but i'll try to keep everything vague.First of all, this game is hard as ♥♥♥♥. Since you have to do everything to the beat of the music (which is sometimes 140 BPM or more) you either have to predict what's going to happen or have the reaction time of a goddess. However, I feel like the difficulty is smoothed over nicely between each zone, and the game gives you plenty of opportunities to practice.I've realized, since I started playing this game, that my reaction time has gotten better by tenfolds. Something that would've been impossible for me before is now easy. So if you want to work on improving your natural reaction time, and have fun while you do it, you should definitely look into getting this game.Other than that, the music in the game literally improves with the difficulty, and changes with every area. I found myself not minding when I had to start over, cause it meant I got to listen to the music again. (spoiler warning) Every unlockable character has their own unique remixes of the zone themes. After you beat the game once, you unlock a special character (along with the second half of the story) that completely revamps all of the songs, making great tunes into masterpieces. I just started playing this character and currently cannot shut up about how awesome all the songs have become.The story, while starting out straightforward and predictable, rewards you after all the difficulty by progressively becoming more in-depth and captivating. Each character has their own story and their own flaws. You discover the stories by playing through the game with each character, which goes on to unlock even more characters with more stories.Overall this game is unique in the way it has singleplayer hours worth of content with non-stop momentum. The one thing i didn't like was the difficulty, but after I finally beat it the hard work was so much more rewarding especially with how fun the newly unlocked character is to play and how much the story evolved."
