76561198037891977,Recommended,247080,29724909,Posted: 5 February,all,robsonclark001,"""Beatdowns to the beat"" from the steam description does a great job of explaining this crazy mashup of genres. A dungeoncrawler with items, monster types, spells, and permadeath. Then throw it for a spin by making every action be done to the beat of the soundtrack. Dash in, Attack, Dodge out, Eat a healing item, Cast a spell, all while keeping to the beat with the handy on screen prompts while keeping the action center stage though.Then what really makes this amazing is after you've played the great default soundtrack, the game can work the same magic on almost any music file you have on your computer. So much fun to do cheesy things like fight a room full of zombies to ""Thriller"", or fight an already shuffling rock golem to ""The Kansas City Shuffle"".Also a solid local co-op to chest bump your friends with!"
