,Recommended,247080,12319487,"Posted: 1 October, 2014",all,Chronon,"Damn this game is difficult to keep up with and I absolutely love the new kind of challenge.Crypt of the Necro Dancer forces the player to think fast which makes even the most simple enemies surprisingly big struggle to kill. Every enemy type has their own pattern but actions are required to be done in rhythm. This keeps the gold multiplier up and the cash flow coming in for better items.Most of the runs last between around 5 to 10 minutes so this game is perfect for short sessions (but I often end up playing for couple of hours on a one go).Before buying this game be wardned that it really is brutal. Many deaths only require 2 hits from some enemies so often even one big enough mistake tends to be deadly. I'm only in the second dungeon and even after 10 hours still struggling to finish it. I'm personally fine with that since the game has only 4 dungeons to complete so far.Btw, local multiplayer is really fun with a right kind of person."
