76561198046180787,Recommended,247080,17583872,"Posted: 17 August, 2015",all,PetrolPatrol (Genji),"At the time of writing this review, I'd only spent 16 hours in this game.Obviously, I'm letting my life go to waste by doing things besides playing this game.-----Okay, but really, for those of you who want a review which may help you decide whether you should buy this game or not (which the answer is yes, btw), here it goes.CotN is a beautiful, rhythm-based dungeon crawler with great graphics (even though they're pixelated), characters, etc. etc. etc. and MUSIC. Holy h*** the music. It's beautiful.There are some bugs which need to be driven out of the game, but there's a very small amount of them. (I've never even run into a bug personally - this is possibly due to my low amount of playtime, but I'm assuming it's just that there are so few bugs left!) As a note, if you find a bug, the developers are very responsive and stay on top of fixing everything.As far as the price goes... it fits the game perfectly. This isn't some game you'll win in a few hours, nor is it a game that you'll get tired of any time soon. You can spend a large amount of time playing, dying over and over and over (and over and over) and not get bored. Now, you may get irritated by how difficult this game is and quit - you'll be back in a few hours at the most, though, don't worry. Due to the difficult nature of the game, you'll probably get a lot of playtime building up just trying to complete every level once! Even with that out of the way, there'll still be more game to explore, and I'm sure you'll be tempted to play the levels over again simply because ""I loved that one enemy,"" or ""I never got that one character you unlock in that level,"" or ""That level had the best music, I need to hear it again,"" and so on.My point is that there's enough time, fun, and replayability (Is that a word? If not, it is now. I made it.) to this game to fit its $15 price tag. Heck, I would have paid more.There's plenty of content to this game as well. This included everything, from the numerous characters you can unlock, to the different store items you can buy that appear in the crypt afterwards, to the numerous enemies and bosses you'll have to learn to fight... Yeah, I could go on and on with that one. Also, levels have a randomized design every time you enter, so you'll always find different items that you've purchased, maybe some new enemies you have yet to face... Fun!One of the best parts of this game is the music. Everything about it is perfect. It always fits the zones you're in so well, for one thing. There's no chance you'll ever feel the music to be tasteless, boring, misfitting, annoying... anything like that. I would definitely buy the soundtrack in its entirety if I had the money (but sadly I spent my monz on the Serious Sam series and CS:GO items so I don't have enough to buy the soundtrack); I'd buy it simply because it's so catchy and it really doesn't grow old.One of the coolest parts of this game besides its music is its level of customization. Now, if you play the game non-stop, falling so deeply in love with it and its music that you forget what the music you used to listen to sounds like, there's a solution for that - in the game's menu, you can go to a submenu (I forget its name at the moment) and choose a level. From there, you can choose a song from your own personal music library and have it uploaded to the game; from there, you can choose whether to have it play at half speed or double speed if you wish, and once you go back to that level you'll get to dance to the beat of your own songs! Also, the Community Workshop for this game has plenty of mods which you can Subscribe to, which will appear under the Mods submenu. Sadly, you can only have one mod active at a time, but it's still pretty neat that you can walk around as a Charizard version of Cadence if you so choose, or even as Luke Triton!As a note, you can kill the Shopkeeper. Just get him angry with something like a bomb, a painful spell, etc., and he'll start chasing after you. Know that if you kill him, you get a hat and all of his merchandise (in this particular store) becomes free. Also know that if you attack him you'd better have a plan because you'll probably die if you don't. I've died so many times to that guy.Before I wrap this up, I'd just like to mention that you can unlock a large variety of characters with their own special quirks/abilities/etc. Cadence is your default character, but you get plenty more options the more you play the game, like Dove, Eli, Bard... yeah that's all I remember at the moment.Anyway, I'm pretty sure I've covered just about everything, so in short, this is a very wonderful game. There's plenty of content, beautiful music, wonderful designs, and just lots and lots of fun to be had. You really do owe it to yourself to try this game at least once. And be warned that if you try it once you'll probably get sucked in."
