,Not Recommended,247080,32795523,Posted: 25 June,all,Oahkery,"For a long, long time, I had this on my ""not interested"" list. But finally, seeing it on sale for $3 and so, so many positive reviews, I thought I'd give it a shot to see if it might surprise me. And sadly, it didn't.It's your typical rouge-like game, plus rhythm, and that's pretty much it. There's nothing to make it stand out other than the fact you have to move on the beat. And that completely turned me off from the game. Within a couple minutes of getting used to the controls, I was already getting tired of being restricted to whatever the tempo of the songs was. If you're traveling through the dungeon or have to backtrack, it's tedious; if you're trying to get to a good spot to attack an enemy and have to keep waiting for the next beat, it can be frustrating. There was absolutely nothing redeeming about the rhythym aspect of the game. The soundtrack was admittedly great, but it could have had a good soundtrack without forcing the rhythym stuff on you.I don't know; maybe I should have listened to my instincts and not bothered with this, but with an ""overwhelmingly positive"" rating and two genres I enjoy, I thought, ""Why not?"" The thing about the game, though, is you get weak versions of both genres that is attempted to be carried by the novelty of combining the two, and that novelty swiftly wears off."
,Not Recommended,247080,26118975,"Posted: 19 October, 2016",all,Bob,"To me this game felt like The Binding of Isaac but to a rhythm. Much like that game this is immensely popular but I don’t like it. The game is deliberately very hard, you are supposed to die repeatedly and each time scrape together enough diamonds to get upgrades to allow you to progress a little further. Despite the procedurally generated levels it grows repetitive and annoying very quickly. Given that this is a music based game, the soundtrack is disappointing. Some of the tracks are great but most of them are forgettable.  The music based combat is novel and the enemies are reasonably varied but not enough to redeem the game for me."
