76561198052392239,Not Recommended,247080,19544711,"Posted: 7 December, 2015",all,SixtusTheFifth,"1/10Why? Because that's how many people finish this game. The global achievements show 7% finish zone 4, which is less than 1/10 but I'll round up.The overwhelmingly positive reviews and the amount of time played are linked.  At the 10 hour mark I would have rated it highly too. But the awful truth, and what no-one has the guts to tell you is: this game hates you.Which would be fine, if it said that on the box or any game reviewer pointed it out. Don't Starve is brutal, Path of Exile is for people who like it tough, Total Biscuit says not to play SpaceChem unless you want to feel stupid; ALL of these game I've played and NONE of them would I give 1/10.But this game doesn't say it on the box, no one points that out and so it gets 1/10 from me.When you start you unlock trainers, you buy items to show up in drops and shops, you unlock training rooms against monsters and bosses. It all seems so promising, like you'll get out what you put in. Welcome to the 10 hour mark, where like every sycophant before you, you too will rate the game 10/10, blather on about the shopkeeper, and not dare say anything bad because the herd decided this developer was one of the good guys.At the 30 hour mark you'll realise: it doesn't matter how much health you buy it never shows up in drops or shops, the training rooms are 1v1 but in the zones you will be mercilessly ganked (one wrong move could put you in a room with 4 minibosses for which there is no training, and two super boss fights spawn mini bosses like mad), and that shopkeeper everyone loves will kill you if you happen to open the door without noticing the colour of the bricks on his shop, perhaps because you were too busy noticing 8 other ways to die.Play the Bard, the herd say, for you can move whenever you like and it is easier. Except that 4.2% have finished the game as the Bard and I'm one of them. The other 95.8% were probably too busy writing overwhelmingly positive reviews.This game hates you, it is trying to kill you, it wants you to fail. Know that.And now you can decide if this is the game for you."
