,Not Recommended,247080,18436419,"Posted: 11 October, 2015",all,Tyler,"Music: Fan-freakin-tasticBosses: Amazing. Really neat ideas with themGameplay: BadDon't get me wrong, I do enjoy the rhythm based movement. That isn't the problem. The problem is the frustrating as hell enemies when you get to the later stages (3+). The first two stages were good. Enemies weren't completely cheap at this point, and the difficulty curve was really nice. However, once you get to stage 3, forget all that. Forget difficulty curves. Enemies here are awful, and most of them seem to be impossible to kill without taking damage, at least consistently.For example, there's some ghost lady who shows up and makes you deaf or something when she touches you. I haven't found a way to even damage her without being hit.Remember vanilla Diablo 3, when you reached Inferno for the first time and you hit a wall of complete ♥♥♥♥ing ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t preventing you from moving on, and there was nothing you could do about it other than get lucky or horribly exploit flaws in the game? Well, that's stage 3 and 4 in Crypt of the Necrodancer.Challenging games are a lot of fun to me, Dark Souls 1 and 2 are two of my favorite games to play, but this game takes it to the frustrating kinds of challenging and not the fun kinds.This games totally worth it on a sale just to enjoy the first two levels, the music, and those first few boss battles. But nothing else."
76561197999822185,Not Recommended,247080,32035027,Posted: 28 May,all,Deeta,"To enjoy this game, you must be able to think on your feet at a snap of the finger. Try as I might, I couldn't do so consistently enough to enjoy the game and it's in fact more stressful than fun.The game compels you to move according to the beat - the longer you're able to do so, the larger the multiplier which affects gold drops from enemies. Some items also benefits from this multiplier. If you try to move when not on the beat, you won't budge at all and your multiplier resets. I found this to be the most unforgiving aspect. Too often I'll just walk into the enemies' attack because I couldn't recall / predict their attack pattern before the beat falls. Having multiple enemies coming at you makes this a lot worse. There is no setting to adjust the tempo to a comfortable level either."
