,Not Recommended,247080,17761459,"Posted: 28 August, 2015",all,jgjfjjfjh,"Being restricted to acting on the beat hurts this game in more than one way. During the beginning zone, where you know the simple enemy patterns like the back of your hand, boredom takes over your senses as you're waiting to move. For the third and fourth zones, the beat gets so fast you'll make mistakes from the stress of needing to think quickly.The simple solution to this problem is to ignore the core gameplay and play as the Bard, right? Wrong. Omitting the rhythm mechanic leaves you with little choice or complexity compared to most traditional roguelikes. If you're in the camp that has no sense of rhythm or don't enjoy the idea of being under a time limit, Crypt of the NecroDancer has nothing for you.Instead, here is a short list of FREE alternatives. These are not as difficult to play as you might be led to believe. After giving an honest effort to learn the controls for 15 minutes, you should be good to go.BrogueDoomRLDungeon Crawl Stone SoupFrozen DepthsInfra ArcanaPowderSil"
