,Not Recommended,247080,19904652,"Posted: 24 December, 2015",all,Pidgin can't right click,"As a game, NecroDancer is great.  The gameplay is novel and appealing, and the rhythmic combat works because of its premise and visual design.  The writing and voices are the opposite: tired and uninspired. The introduction was so clumsy and full of flat monologue attempting to be snarky that I questioned if the gameplay is worth it.  At the second story sequence it just continues ruining what otherwise would have been a great roguelike without exposition interrupting play.  From what I saw online, the narrative was written by Silverstring Media.  I think the game could have been better with the developers' own ideas than diluting it with others' visions.I can't recommend it at its asking price of $15."
,Not Recommended,247080,33287862,Posted: 5 July,all,An Angry Yordle,"I love RoguelikesI love Rythm GamesI don't like Crypt of the NecrodancerSo why is that?So hear me out, don't just leave a thumb down, I hope you'll be willing to listen even if you like the game.Well, here's some points:1. Unappealing GraphicsI love good Pixelart...I really do, but this mostly isn't good one.The artists are using the same colour for too many pixels on many images, making it look very very old fashioned. Some look good but too many don'tIf you wanna see really good Pixelart go check out Stardew Valley, Nuclear Throne, or Starbound, they all have their own take on Pixelart and they all look gorgeous. Sadly, CotND doesn't.2. Unnatural DifficultyThe game forces you to make quick decisions.There is not a single time you can have a break, except for maybe switching between two tiles in an empty room.For a game that mostly has a puzzle take on Roguelikes this isn't good, since you barely can concentrate and are gonna panic move a lot which just leads to unnecessary frustration.If you wanna see difficult, but non-frustrating games check out the Dark Souls series, Nuclear Throne, Super Meat Boy, Geometry Dash, The Witness...and many many more, there seriously is a lot of them!3. Lack of information given to the playerThe tutorial doesn't show you how to use items and how the gold multiplier works, enemy health and strength aren't shown, so you either have to remember or guess. Items in the shop aren't explained, so you never know what you're buying, neither are alternative gamemodes.The game really needs to get a little more polished.4. Lack of contentLet's compare to other Roguelikes.The Binding of Isaac: Rebirth has a huge amount of different and unique items, enemies, playable characters and gamemodes, also a lot of them you have to unlock through certain actions.Rogue Legacy has a big Skilltree, many character traits and a fluent progress system.Faster than Light has a huge learning curve, and also a big amount of upgrades and unlockables.Nuclear Throne got at least a decent amount of weapons, playable characters, character perks and secrets, but therefore it still beats CotND in almost every other cathegory and takes long enough to play through anyways, due to its difficulty.So where's any of that in CotND? At least one thing should be worked out deeply.5. The soundtrack is good, but...other Roguelikes got great OST too.Okhlos: Omega for example got way better one in my opinion and even other Roguelikes like The binding of Isaac, Dead Cells or Nuclear Throne can keep up with CotNDTo Masterpiece Soundtracks like the ones of Dear Esther, Clannad, Rabi-Ribi or the Final Fantasy games it's not comparable at all and unlike them this is a music game!6. And for the Rhythm game side of thingsThere's simply better ones. Point. Ones where you don't have to solve a puzzle while keeping the Rhythm, ones where you're not feeling like a metronome after 5 minutes.Check out Geometry Dash, Osu, DDR or Final Fantasy Theatrhythm...and guess what: Osu and DDR and Geometry Dash let you add your own music too.In addition it's one of those games with a horrible DLC policy, I mean, the soundtrack (split among multiple DLC's) costs more than the actual game, who did get that idea?I mean, CotND is not a bad game, but it's average at most and heavily overrated."
