,Not Recommended,247080,33494403,Posted: 12 July,all,Alex Schaus,"Ultimately this was not rewarding for me. If there was a demo, I'd have quickly dismissed this without buying the entire game. Clearly the rhythm mechanic of pushing up/down/left/right is of interest to many, given the number of positive reviews, but it's nonetheless lost on me.I enjoy rogue-like games, in the Dead Cells sense...and I enjoy the fun of learn, die, repeat. But the learning in this game consists of dancing around and into monsters with particular movement patterns in order to hit without being hit back. Movement is inherently limited by this design, and I found no ""aha"" moments where some particular pattern or combination was particularly fun to execute.Contrast this with other rogue-likes where one is rewarded, especially in the beginning, with new and interesting tactics and options to explore and find a playstyle that fits and rewards the player for their own creativity.Sadly, such is not the case for this game, due to the nature of the limited mobility and incessant pulsing beat that feels as if it is playing you.Would very much like my money back so I can risk it on something else in the rogue-like genre."
