76561198034525914,Not Recommended,247080,19908780,"Posted: 24 December, 2015",all,Got Baking Soda? #Dicks Out,"I love this game so much - YogcastThe trailer of this game just goes to show us that this indie dev is willing to drop their standards to the corporate ♥♥♥♥♥ that is the Yogcast network on youtube.If I was paying atention and looked at that trailer I knew that this was going to be a mediocre game. When I played I was correct. Just another indie game that has a gimmick/mechanic feature in the game to keep people playing.Unfortunately if you are deaf you can play this game with the beating hearts on the screen but you also need to be aware of the action that happens on a rudimentary 1x4 block system for map movement. This is counterintuitive and any competent developer could have made a system for deaf people if they were going to want to play this screen.The story well... the intro video told me nothing. More and more games go away giving context and are hiding it in obscure places believing we are archaeologists wanting to figure this IMPORTANT stuff out... We don't want to. Japanese game design at its finest. Disagree with me go play a japanese game right now or any Japanese game in any console generation and you will find some gems that give next to no context on anything. Then write back to me if I am not wrong.Okay back to review the game is a gimmick. As I stated before indie devs base their games off little gimmick features for the majority of the time. It works for sales and it looks ORIGINAL. Some work, some don't. The main feature of this game does not work and I only had to play it for ten minutes to figure that out because I knew that it could not add much more onto that system.Last note. Developers please do not puch patch notes before the main menu of the game screen. If I am interested in knowing the changes to the game put in a menu option, which you can do but please do not put it before the menu. New players look at that and will think wtf. Before you even play a game in 2015 you  have to go through 5 - 6 screens before you got to the game. Learn to figure simple things like that out. Not hard. Also that loading screen at the start of the game is too long for a pc to load up. Do your job better."
76561198055981406,Not Recommended,247080,18445627,"Posted: 12 October, 2015",all,majinsteph,"I don't recommend this game if you are like me, and are looking for a game to play with your dance pad that has the feel of a dance game, but with rogue-like dungeon crawling elements.  This game is all rogue-like, with none of the physical, rhythmical feeling that comes with playing most dance pad games.  The art and music in this game are amazing, and it is a pretty fun rogue-like when I put the dance pad away and just play with my keyboard...but that's not what I bought the game for so I doubt I will be finishing it.  Playing with the dance pad makes the game much harder, and there is a dance pad mode that is supposed to make the game easier, but it still wasn't all that fun.  Before the Echo is more the kind of game I was looking for.  So if you are mostly a DDR/ITG/etc fan with not much interest in rogue-like games, don't be fooled by the images and videos of dance pads...this game is not really designed to be optimally played on one."
