76561198009071862,Not Recommended,247080,17582785,"Posted: 17 August, 2015",all,DesuCat ♥,"I think you are better off just buying the soundtrack (which is just absolutely amazing) and leaving this game alone.The whole randomized levels thing isn't very well implemented. You start with the same items on every level you often end up severely lacking in some resource, be it a weapon, healing items, armour, shovel etc. It also leads to a lot of shenanigans such as: Starting off right next to the miniboss (all of which have a near global aggro range btw) and a bunch of tought to kill cronies, teleporting into 5+ mobs most likely leading to death because the monsters stepped onto the floor switch but haven't moved off the destination spot, and the ole classic ""Shopkeeper's on fire"". The whole beat gameplay thing is fun for a while, and it is, but late game enough you are better off ignoring it since you get plenty of gold without needlessly putting yourself at risk. I think it's kind hilarious that a lot of the monsters will move/attack to the beat as well, sometimes putting you in a bad spot as long as you are playing the game the way it's meant to be played. That makes it seem near discouraged. This may sounds a bit mean, but the cutscenes are quite poorly made, I would even go as far as compare them to Zelda CDI games. Of course they don't stoop to that level but the resemblance is very strong. I don't expect something insane from a 15 dollar indie game, but there are other ways of adding story content without excess animation, take the old school dialogue box scenes they used a lot in RPGs in them good ole days. Voice acting is pretty odd, I'm currently playing as the protagonist (the game does feature a variety of playable characters), female character Cadence and her voice seems to change during battle, certain spells and hits from certain attacks will cause her to sounds like a deep voiced bloke. Peace."
76561197992574468,Not Recommended,247080,24944026,"Posted: 15 August, 2016",all,SLAVomir Peszko,"I have no idea why everyone is so positive about this game. I was also really hyped for it, but it turned out to be quite a mediocre experience for me. Why?1. This is a rythm based game and music is soooo forgetable (i know that you can play your own music, but i'm speaking about vanilla program here). I mean like, COME ON! I'm sorry Danny Baranovsky, you are an exeptional indie composer, but this isn't your magnum opus for sure.2. The game is repetetive as hell. I know it is a roguelike, and you should just die and do the♥♥♥♥♥♥again and again, and its fine. But there is just too little content in it especially comparing it to something like The Binding of Isaac (which also is a proof that Baranovsky can do musch better this in terms of music). The variety of the enemies is ok, but few bosses and weapons is waaaaay too little. You just find particular weapon as early as possible and stick to it to the end. You can also find spells and clothing, but most of it are generic stuff like fireballs and armor. Also there are permanent upgrades like health and items, but there is also very little of that (I unlocket all of it in like 3 hours ir so).3. ZZZzzzZZZ Tempo of this game is bad. First levels are slow and when you go further and further termpo of the music increases. On paper it makes sense. But ""in reality"" it means that you have to play easy, slow, first levels over and over again just to die quickly later. Almost every roguelike suffers from this in some degree, but this one especially, because music dictates your movement speed (unless you play overpowered bard).I admit, I played this game with base character for only some time, than I just finished it with Bard in 2 hours (it turns into more of a puzzle game with this character), and lack of content discoureged me from playing again. Maybe there is some more stuff, but Wiki seems to be confirming my worries.5/10"
