,Recommended,247080,17674638,"Posted: 23 August, 2015",all,Hopyoprop,"Crypt of the Necrodancer is a refreshing indie game to hit the market and is defintely worth every penny spent. It is a rhythm rougue like bolstering a unique gameplay. Every enemy including you moves according to the beat of the music and the faster the music, the harder the level is. There is 4 zones for each character, each showcasing it's unique enemies with interesting attack patterns as well.Although people may say that 4 zones may be little for a game but there are multiple characters to test your skills in the 4 zones. This game looks easy but is no joke. It's a tough rhythm rougue like challenging your fast thinking and reaction time. Many characters change the gameplay such as:1. Die in a single beat, only dagger as a weapon.2. 2x Speed of music3. Jump 2 spaces instead of one all the time.4. Cannot pick up money.5. Cannot kill anything.6. Can only use bombs to attack.7. etc.It also includes a character that the developers say that is almost impossible to complete (he is extremely difficult) but one person on youtube has already. This game offers so much enjoyment and the Original Sountrack by Danny Baranowsky, A-Rival and FamilyJules7x all offer a good accompaniment. Even after you get tired of the original soundtrack, custom music from your own libraries are also supported in this game.If you are tired of the keyboard, get a dancepad and get onto your feet. This game has support for dancepads and even have official ones just for this game and if you're game for it, go get it and try!Overall, this game offers a full package and experience as an indie game and was a refreshing entry to the indie game scene and if you are looking for something unique yet really enjoyable to play, this game is for you!Would I recommend this? ABSOLUTELY YES."
