,Recommended,247080,17661739,"Posted: 22 August, 2015",all,RicePrezPip,"You thought Dark Souls and Binding of Isaac were tough? Then, MAN, are you in for a challenge. This game is so goddamn amazing I can barely put it into words. On top of randomly generated fun, the game has fantastic pixel graphics, hours of replayibility and some of the best music I've ever heard anywhere, making the rhythm based gameplay 800% more fun. (Or you could just play Bard like a loser.)I find this game harder than Dark Souls & Isaac for 2 reasons. 1. Unlike Isaac it doesn't seem possible to become so OP you one shot every boss before they can even blink. 2. The game isn't as generous as Isaac is with health drops. Unless you find a drumstick or a blood weapon, you're not getting that health back.Only bad thing I have to say about this game is the lack of attack animations make some enemies difficult to read, you'll have to rely on the beats of the song (unless you're going up against those irritating goblins, which I hate). It's somewhat frustrating losing a decent run because I couldn't tell if the enemy was about to swing or not. I also consider the lack of health drops a problem, but chances are I'm just awful at the game.Buy this. Now."
