,Recommended,247080,13175969,"Posted: 30 November, 2014",all,phen⏣l,"When I first heard of Crypt of the NecroDancer, I immediately dismissed it because I figured a roguelike rhythm game would never be able to satisfactorily be both.  I was very, very wrong.This game is one of the best roguelikes and one of the best rhythm games I've ever played.  As expected, there's a huge amount of depth and complexity to the game, and the procedural generation and breadth of items in the game mean that it really scratches that roguelike itch.  But it's also an equally compelling rhythm game -- the music is superb, the mechanics are top-notch, and it's amazing when you can finally feel the beat and handle each enemy with your eyes closed.Also, if you're squeamish because it's Early Access, worry not -- there are very regular updates (both bugfixing and content), the game is playable, stable, and very fun in its current state, and the dev team itself is very responsive."
