,Recommended,247080,13474616,"Posted: 20 December, 2014",all,Variance,"This game is simply lovely. The music is hauntingly catchy, the graphic style is  perfect for the genre, and the play control is solid.The whole game takes some simple concepts and weaves them in to a hybrid game that offers hours of enjoyment.You are descending a dungeon, collecting items and slaying monsters along the way. The catch is, you're doing this to the rhythm of the dungeon.  Learning how each monster moves and attacks is simple enough - however making the right movement choices while you're under the threat of missing a beat is not always so easy.  This keeps the game fast paced and engaging.True to roguelike form, the game has tons of little things that keep it interesting, spells, items, secret shops etc. allowing for many viable strategies for your dungeon delve. Once you master the game, you can unlock more characters to play as, each one with a unique attribute that will change how you play the game. I'm sure I will continue to play this for well over 100 hours. Easily one of my best purchases on Steam, bang for buck.The developer updates have been constant and excellent. So no fear of this getting abandoned anytime soon."
