76561197989740730,Recommended,247080,17858098,"Posted: 2 September, 2015",all,OWLS,"Rhythm roguelike.  The game is essentially a turn-based roguelike where every beat of the music is a turn.  You and your enemies can only take action on the beats of the music.  There are a variety of weapons that all function differently and enemies all follow certain patterns to the beat.  As you would expect of a game that relies on rhythm, the soundtrack is great.  You can also play the game to your own music if you prefer.  There are multiple characters that play differently or offer up different challenges.  There are seeded runs and daily challenge runs with leaderboards.  This is a great game for anyone that likes roguelikes."
,Recommended,247080,30520482,Posted: 14 March,all,glasnerven,"Short version: this game is really fun (but hard!) and has no obvious flaws.Longer version: I like everything about this game. The music is great--I know I could replace it with my own music, but why would I want to? The pixel art is perfect. The gameplay is simple, clean, and sharp. You want replay value? The characters all play similar enough to draw on your previous experience, yet differently enough to keep it fresh. You can even do couch co-op!The difficulty level could be a little daunting, maybe, but through my many, many deaths I always felt like it was fair, and like the game wasn't punishing me, but challenging me to meet my potential.If the idea of a rhythm/roguelike mashup sounds like it could be fun if it were done well, you should get this game, because it's done VERY well."
