,Recommended,247080,15704160,"Posted: 5 May, 2015",all,Whaleton,"At a basic glance, this seems fairly simple. Move to the beat, advance like any other roguelike. However, this game is much harder then it seems, and I find myself dying a lot and then thinking ""I should have seen that coming"". One of my pet peeves in roguelikes are enemies that I get immensely frustrated with because of RNG or hard-to master attacks. However, this game's enemies all follow fairly easy to learn patterns, and it's mainly a matter of recognizing those patterns. The weapons in the game are all interesting, with different playstyles being offered in the first few levels to start off; the different weapon variants keep it interesting. Compounded with the soundtrack by DannyB, this game is amazing. I've found myself saying ""Just one more run"" over and over again. The 10 different characters all offer unique playstyles, even if some are less fun then others. The variety, mechanics, and options in the game allow for hours of fun. If I had one minor complaint, it seems like the ""unlocking"" method for the various lobby NPCs seem somewhat pointless. It'd probably be better to just have to unlock them with diamonds instead of golden/glass keys. All in all, an amazing game that I would reccommend to anyone who enjoys roguelikes or pain."
