76561198030905849,Recommended,247080,16162466,"Posted: 3 June, 2015",all,Game Soup,"This game will suck you in, hook, line, and sinker, especially if you like RPGs, rhythm games, or roguelikes.  It has virtually infinite replay value, the difficulty is perfectly balanced (I have never died unless it was my fault), and the mechanics could take a lifetime to master and perfect.  This is the most fun I've had with any single game in many years.  There is more content than some triple-A titles, more replayability than most other small developer games, and more polish than I have ever seen in a title of this size.  Each round can last as long as 30 minutes or as short as 5 seconds if you aren't careful, and each time you play you'll learn a little more about mastering the game's world.It took me 24 hours to beat beat the first 2/3 of the story, and I've spent 30 more working on the last 1/3 as well as playing with all the other characters.  The daily challenge, all zones modes, all characters mode, unlockable items, and characters give you so much to do!  I'm almost 60 hours in and haven't unlocked all the characters.  You will NOT get bored of this game.I can't recommend this game enough!  It's my ""stranded on an island game,"" and I anticipate that with mods and the level editor, you could literally play this game for years and never get bored of it.  I've never played a game that I sunk 50 hours into and still couldn't wait to get home and play some more, and the music is one of the best soundtracks an indie title could have.  The game sets a new standard for rhythm-based games and for hectic fun."
