,Recommended,247080,16339686,"Posted: 12 June, 2015",all,kailoto17,"Rhythm. Roguelike. Two fantastic genres on their own, and yet here, they come together and form something entirely unique.Since it's part rhythm game, you'd expect the music to be good. Well, it is. Almost too much so. Danny Baranowsky delivers a killer OST, but the remixes by A_Rival and FamilyJules7x are of equal caliber. Adding your own music is always welcome in rhythm games, and this game makes it easy and fun to expiriment around with different tracks.And the roguelike aspect is just as polished. One of the best things about CotND is that it feels fair, in the way that many roguelikes don't; you never feel at the mercy of the RNG god, and nearly every death is something you could have avoided with more skill. The weapons and items allow for a variety of different playstyles, ensuring that gameplay remains fresh.Other things of note: There's lots of stuff to unlock and ten different characters to play as, each with their own playstyle, so for those worried that it'll be a shallow experience, fear not; I've been playing it for many hours and it still hasn't gotten stale. The story is actually quite engaging, and the final chapter is immensely difficult but exceedingly rewarding.Easily the most innovative game I've ever seen, polished to perfection. If either rhythm or roguelikes are your thing, don't miss out on this one folks."
