,Recommended,247080,22806520,"Posted: 5 May, 2016",all,Authentic Hater,"Fantastic, brutally hard rhythm combat dungeon crawly RPG. Different characters completely change the way the game is played with their own unique challenges. Want to take your time? Play bard, who is not bound to the rhythm of the music. Want to kill nothing and tickle enemies with your flower power? Dove. Want to be challenged to your absolute limit? Try Coda, who plays at double speed, dies in one hit, dies when picking up gold, dies when missing a single beat, and has an extremely limited item pool.Success in the game is earned through patience and learning the patterns of each enemy - many enemies brutally punish being mindlessly charged, with a few beats of reckless attacking quickly seeing you dead and furious.Bosses are fun and challenging, but true strategy is not required for most of them when playing the easier characters, as a good collection of items can see you downing bosses in one bar of music. The story progresses through increasingly difficult characters with the final character being substantially harder than those before. It's a difficulty spike, but by the time you reach it you'll feel a possessed determination to reach the end at all costs, inspired by the previous four hours of relentless beats infecting your mind and demanding you complete the NecroDance of Destiny.Barrier of entry is moderate - non-gamers or the rhythmically (or physically) impaired may have trouble sticking with the game until it 'clicks' for them. Bard allows everyone to enjoy the puzzley elements of the game and practice for harder characters, and there are practice rooms available for absolutely every enemy type and boss; so those goddamned red dragons can stop slaughtering you on your otherwise perfect run.Session time is short, with levels being 2-5 minutes in length, three levels a zone with a boss at the end of each.I planned to make this a two minute silly review, but this game deserved justice.Charming as F**K, could not recommend more."
