,Recommended,247080,22773188,"Posted: 2 May, 2016",all,Vahn,"This game is solid, and a lot of fun. Once you realize that moving to the rythm is critical and not staying calm is the reason you are getting killed (fighting those instinct to button mash those monsters to death), the game becomes very fun to play and has a very interesting difficulty curve.Each new area spikes in difficulty temporarily as you adjust to the new enemy patterns and item mechanics, and adds a great deal of satisfaction to finally being able to beat it.All of the soundtracks are great, and you can even add your own music easily through the in-game menu, but beware- the beat that the game recognizes for your own music can sometimes be very unnatural to your percieved rhythm of the song and make it very difficult to play. Test the beats in the lobby first before you venture out with your own songs.5/5 for this game delivering what it promises.6/5* if they added a metronome-style, hit-the-spacebar-to-the-tempo adjustment to custom songs.Will definitely listen to this soundtrack when I drive around town again."
