,Recommended,247080,19088271,"Posted: 14 November, 2015",all,dimestore thriller™,"A fairly straightforward roguelike dungeon crawler, with the main selling point being the way the game is built around music and timing. You can only move one sqaure at a time in time with the music, and the enemies are similarily constrained. As you progress you upgrade your character through vendors and unlock new ones. NecroDancer also has the ability to add your own music to the game, and a 2 player local multiplayer, both of which are worthwhile additions, and help to add length to what may only be a novelty game for some, given it's simplicity. Necrodancer is neither a masterful dungeon crawler or a superb rhythm game, but when combined, it leads to a game I would encourage anyone to try."
