76561198113753579,Recommended,247080,19716455,"Posted: 15 December, 2015",all,Chasey Failnaut,"This review is mainly just so the developers can see.This game is great. I love the concept, the execution is good, despite being a bit slow-paced during certain songs, and it's got a nice difficulty, as well. It's fun to try to make it through a zone, and it's very satisfying to complete one. There were a few things that seemed like game breaking at first. As it turns out, they're not. With the exception of the Bard (who is extremely fun to play as), all characters that I've unlocked so far will drop to the next floor once the song is over. So no worries about being stuck.If I happen to find anything that should probably be fixed, I'll post it here right away. For now, here are some tips:1. The Crown of Teleportation is a potentially extremely useful item that will warp you to the shop (if one is available) upon being hit, but only once. If this item sends you to a shop that requires a bomb to access, and you don't have any bombs, no enemies can hit you anymore. This is great for all characters except for the Bard, due to the automatic drop to the next floor when a song ends.2. The Boots of Leaping cause you to move two tiles per beat instead of one. This is rarely useful, but wait! There's more! Turns out you can toggle these! This turns a run-breaking, bad item into an amazing item that can potentially allow you to escape nearly any battle in just a few beats. I didn't know this until recently because I wasn't paying attention to the HUD. Note to self: Always check th e HUD.Easy 9/10 for me.Oh, and did I mention that the local co-op is amazing?And the best part: THE DEVS ACTUALLY READ ALL OF THEIR REVIEWS AND COMMENTS!Such precious few dev teams actually take the time to read their reviews and respond in turn, so it's really nice that Brace Yourself Games is willing to do so. I respect that."
