76561198055439193,Recommended,247080,11645379,"Posted: 10 August, 2014",all,Hectorlph,"Should you buy this game?The answer is YES if any of the following apply:1. You like rhythm games. Nothing is more satisfying for a rhythm gamer than a game that is dynamic, and not just about memorizing. You have to react to what the games throws at you.2. You like dungeon crawler games. This is one of the best games when it comes to replay value, in my opinion. There are so many different things to try. I played over 30 hours in alpha/beta, and I am definitely going to spend another 20+ just trying out new builds on my character or creating new dungeon maps.3. You like skill based games. Seriously, this game takes some skill to master. So many different situations to overcome. There are even multiple characters and modes to play in to make it even more of a challenge!My experience:I played this game in early access, and it was an absolute blast of a game! Updates were frequent and so much quality content was being added. The rhythm mechanics are great, the different weapons make it fun to play over and over, and the boss fights are sublime.About 6 months ago, I stopped playing because I didn't have time anymore.I just came back today after the main update, and wow, I have some things to say. This game is even better than I could have possibly thought. I don't normally write reviews twice on games, but I'll make an exception for COTND. I just started to stratch the surface of the new characters, items, and bosses. So far, I am LOVING it. I don't feel overwhelmed by new content at all, in fact I am enjoying discovering new items and enemies. The story mode is just what the game needed--something to tie together the characters, bosses, and theme of the game. I can't wait to play this a ton over the summer!"
