76561198087435307,Recommended,247080,18462039,"Posted: 13 October, 2015",all,NintendoPlayerSega,"Ever wanted to listen to some of your favorite tunes while also occasoinally raging at a game? Well then Crypt of the Necrodancer is for you! As a rouge-like rhythm game with RPG elements, the game is a blast to play through. However, as  I said, this game is no joke. Learning to get used to moving during the song's rhythm is already hard enough but having to deal with enemies at the same time will have you make sure you're paying attention, as it is easy to get lost in what's happening. The first 2 zones of th game are good at easing you into the game without things getting too crazy. That all changes when you reach the third and fourth zones which contain enemies with special movement and attack patterns that will make sure you remember what they do. The third and fourth zones also show a problem with the game. The layout of the levels and the enemies can sometimes be overwhelming and sometimes unfair, but not enought to the point where you'll want to rage quit. The variety of items that can be obtained in the game while not as high as games like Binding of Isacc: Rebirth, is still rather high and also plays a good role in how a zone run can play out for you. Also, the song generator is so much fun to use. Each song has it's own speed and can be adjusted if one thinks its either too slow or too fast. There's also a level editor that allows usage of all the game's assets and can these levels can also be submitted to the Steam Workshop. One more thing, aside from dungeons, the mod community for this game is massive! Mods for the game were even made during the game's beta and are still being made even to this day. Crypt of the Necrodancer, while not the most forgiving game, is one of the most enjoyable rhythm games out there if you like those kinds of games in addition to rouge-like games."
