76561198025037205,Recommended,247080,17953018,"Posted: 8 September, 2015",all,heywowlookitsme,"I cannot say enough good things about this game. The concept is ingenious- stylishly blend rythm elements into a turn pseudo turn-based dungeon crawler, complete with adorable dancing monsters and one of the most enjoyable soundtracks I have heard from a video game.Combat and movement works really well with the rythm based system- especially since there is a little more leway than in most rythm based games. The game impliments a roughly 60% accuracy threshhold for staying on beat, meaning the game doesnt penalize you for being slightly off the beat. This is somewhat necessary: because the game throws so much at you (especially in the later levels), managing the traps, monsters and staying on beat at the same time would be too much for new players.The levels are procedurally generated, which means that you will never play the same map twice (any dungeon crawler that doesnt include this feature should be uninstalled immediately)The monsters and environments are really vibrant and unique- The boss battles really feel epic and stand apart from one another (Its not just a bigger or more powerful version of monsters you have already faced)The sheer number of items in the game bring meaningful variety to how you approach different enemies, and keep the game fresh.Overall, this has quickly become one of my favorite games and I just cant stop telling people about it."
