,Recommended,247080,11500534,"Posted: 31 July, 2014",all,CJ The Expert,"It's just another turn based dungeon-crawler. Except that this time, you don't dictate when a turn is, the music does. No time to mull over your choices, the fast pace pushes you onward, only to dash your hopes against a skeleton (or, more embarassingly, a slime). The simple, four button countrol scheme is somehow turned into movement, attack, magic, and inventory in a way that isn't at all confusing, surprisingly. And it's hella fun.Great rougelike, definitely worth the cash. Hard as nails, but in a less frustrating way. Thankfully, you can watch a replay of your run, and see EXACTLY where you messed up. Very helpful. The music is far above what you might expect. And you can replace it with your own, if that tickles your fancy.9/10. Only thing keeping it from being a 10/10 is that it's not done yet."
