76561198006745609,Recommended,247080,14253270,"Posted: 30 January, 2015",all,Cyclone Jack,"Very entertaining game with a great soundtrack (and inspiring vocals).  If you like rhythm games and rogue-likes, then I would recommend picking this up, as it combines the two quite well.  Most of the game revolves around moving to the beat of the music while defeating a wide variety of enemies, all of which have their own movement patterns that you need to figure out.  Levels get progressively more difficult, and the boss fights are fun and creative.There are also a number of other characters to unlock and play as, each of which has their own style of play.  One character dies as soon as he touches gold, which forces you to rethink how/where you kill enemies (since they all drop gold), another character is not bound by the constrainst of the music (free move), while another is a pacificst and cannot attack enemies at all.  Each of these, and more, bring with them their own challenges, and keep the game interesting."
