,Recommended,247080,13265753,"Posted: 7 December, 2014",all,Atara,"Even in its current Early Access state, Crypt of the NecroDancer is an extremely fun albeit challenging game. By far the most outstanding aspect of the game is the excellent soundtrack, which I would recommend purchasing in addition to the game. The art is also quite nice, featuring a colorful, beautifully-animated pixel style. The gameplay is fun, addicting, and challenging. You get used to only moving on the beat very quickly. However there is a steep learning curve in understanding how to conquer each enemey, especially when you are using the default dagger as your main weapon. Thankfully, it is possible to train against specific enemies from the lobby screen.  The game does employ a rogue-like perma-death mechanic. However, I did not find this too frustrating, because after each death, the player accumulates gems that can be used to purchase permanent upgrades that persist through all of your subsequent replays. This helps the player feel like they are making progress even when they are repeatedly failing on a level.All in all, an extremely fun, addicting game with a wonderful soundtrack!"
