76561198036268470,Recommended,247080,15591232,"Posted: 27 April, 2015",all,hotlimit1,"-Hop to the beat of a great original soundtrack, or use your own music to traverse the dungeon and wreck enemies!-Lots of unique items and enemies with an interesting method of progression.-Crammed with content including different characters and several practice stages, so you can master the game's strategy without pressure.This is a brilliant title that stands among the greats of innovative music-driven games like Rez and Patapon. By combining the fundamentals of rogue-likes (perma-death, situational and experienced-based strategy) and Tetsuya Mizuguchi-style synesthesia (Rez, Lumines), NecroDancer provides a brand-new gaming experience that is not only engaging but endlessly addictive. As with any good rogue-like, the game includes enough unique items to discover and new enemy types to plot against to make the game last far beyong a single completion.While the game does include a fantastic soundtrack featuring a great variety of music, one of the game's best features is the ability to customize the soundtrack with your own (MP3-format) music. Using a simple in-game menu to navigate files on your hard drive, you can replace the music for each dungeon floor, boss, and the lobby. A program within the game will automatically find the BPM of your songs, effectively modifying each section of the game to create a unique experience. I would recommend having a listen to the game's original soundtrack a few times, but the custom soundtrack option should not be overlooked."
