,Recommended,247080,11504125,"Posted: 1 August, 2014",all,Shi~Kyle,"10/10 would recommend.This game is in early access but it has so much content to work with. Crrypt of the Necrodancer for Four zones in the game, each eith 3 stages and a boss per zone with their own different change of enemies, enemy varients, enviroments and music to go with them as-well as a small handful of available characters with much more to come, each with their own little gimmick.This game is a rogue-like rhythm strategy game that displays a mechanic like no other game. The mechanic involved moving along to the beat of the provided music, not only moving but also attacking, using items and using spells. The downside to missing the beat is losing a turn which the enemy could take advantage of, the other downside is losing your gold multiplier for successful kills while staying to the rhythm. Like most rogue-likes, each floor layout and enemy is randomly generated.The game features controller support along with Dance Dance Revolution (DDR) mat support (As-long as it can connect to your computer via USB?) The game features a mode to make using the DDR mat easier as using the mat itself in nromal mode would likely be a cripple. The game also features a local co-op game mode, a hardcore mode and a Daily Challenge.EDIT: I can say as a controller user, I have had some problems when I start the game back up, some of the layout of buttons I set for the controller seem to switch to a random button on the controller."
