,Recommended,247080,15514294,"Posted: 23 April, 2015",all,Pink Rockwell,"Like most roguelikes, this game punishes you (though not too much, with the lobby that grants you permanent item upgrades) when you die. You start at the beginning.Unlike most roguelikes, and as stated by one of the developers in the crew video, this game kills you very fairly. Every enemy has a pattern that can be learned and can be exploited, so that you can make it through the game with just your basic weapon. You will know why you died and, while frustrating to start at the beginning, you will find it to be fair.The music is excellent, the singing shopkeeper is awesome. The only complaint isn't really a complaint, it's just that when you start over so many times, the first few level's music gets kind of annoying. I think it would've helped to have a rotation of a few songs on the same beat to keep things fresh, since you'll be hitting the first level a lot as you learn. I know that's a hilarious amount of work, so meh.Excellent game, seizure inducing, great enemies and it feels like a lot has been put into the game so far (Been playing a few hours what do I know)."
