,Recommended,247080,15561439,"Posted: 26 April, 2015",all,Agni7atha,"Do you recommend this game?Absolutely YesThis is a brilliant game idea with a brilliant execution. Mix between roguelike and rhythm was never expected to be this fun. Looks simple in the surface, just four buttons and four level, but actually have a great amount of depth. Training to get better is so rewarding, especially in higher level. You will die often but never feel unfair. You will get the feeling you die because your own mistake, not because RNG. This game probably have the great balanced gameplay. Item or monster are less likely to feel OP, which is rare on rougelike genre.As early access player, I have to say this is a good example how you do an early access game. Developer are active on forum, either on steam forum or their own official forum. Player and developer are working together, mostly on testing new feature and bug tracking. Suggestion from player are taken often. You can check update history if you want. For me, Brace Yourself Games is a trusted game developer and I won't mind jump in to their next early access project if that happening.What surprised me is how good the final release are. First thing to notice is how big the installation size compared to beta build, it's almost four times bigger. After checking the files and trying the game for couple of hours, I realize they are adding cutscene, extra soundtrack, and some finishing touch to the game. It is indeed not relevant to beta testing but I believe it's quite important to final release. It's a good move I would say. The developer are often promised that the final zone, the zone 4, will be released in final build and kept early access player waiting for that. After finishing the zone, with some awesome boss battle, I have to say it's worth the wait. It's feel like a gift from developer to the early access player, to describe how good it is.So the verdict is: You get this game and You never regret it."
