76561198024845688,Recommended,247080,15573114,"Posted: 26 April, 2015",all,Gorban010,"Crypt of the NecroDancer is immediately addictive. The randomly-generated levels create a different play style each time you restart a zone (and you will be restarting very, very often) since you'll find different items in different orders. Most of the time there are strategies to kill each type of enemy without taking damage which makes it sound easy except you'll be doing it to the beats of music and you WILL make mistakes. You get a random boss at the end of each zone so you will have to learn to be consistent going through all the levels in a zone before you can get some real time grinding the bosses (though I think you can do boss training on the zone selection 'overworld', perhaps after you free the correct NPC ??). I often feel I do not have the time to learn the strategy of other roguelikes with unlimited realtime per turn available to strategize, but this game I was able to pick up immediately and it's incredibly fun. I'm sure there is a ton of unique fun to be had even if you do enjoy the in depth strategy of other roguelikes since, likely, you will not have played it to the tempo of music before."
