,Recommended,247080,12851292,"Posted: 8 November, 2014",all,johnrdconnolly,"This game is totally amazing. It Is great in pretty much every way. It's a a rogue-like which means when you die you have to start over. Unless of course you have a magic potion that gives you another life, but more on that later. It is a top down turn by turn grid based dungeon crawler.The game has, as of right now, 3 zones, each with three levels then a random boss level. The levels are randomly generated dungeons where the creatures get more challenging each level, followed by a boss battle, The unique aspect of this game is that a turn happens on the beat of the music, and you get a gold multiplier bonus for moving each turn along with the beat and not getting hurt. Sort of a combo system that gets your more gold. It sounds slightly confusing, but it ends up being a completely unique and awesome gameplay mechanic that makes the game one of the best I have ever played.This brings me to the first point, and that is the totally gnarly soundtrack that never gets old for me. You slay beasts left and right while collecting gnarly loot as you grind through level after level with death just one wrong move away, to a totally grooving soundtrack the whole time. Pure Awesomeness.It is challenging, but if you learn your enemie's movements and attacks, you  can slay dragons, minataurs, and nightmare steads with a few slices of your glass rapier. If going zone by zone you unlock permanent perks through the dungeonmaster, merlin, and hepheastus at the starting area. You can also play hardcore mode which gives you only one attempt to beat all the zones in one run, with all itmes unlocked, but no upgrades from the lobby. THE TRUE TEST OF BEAT SHREDDING MONSTER SLAYING. It'as fantastic.Your character has a bunch of different equipment slots. Head, torch, weapon, armour, legs, ring, and shovel. And each slot has tons of gnarly items that can go in them.There are rings of regeneration, peace, war, protection, might, luck, and phasing just to name some. Each has a unique property that changes your gameplay syle.Ton's of awesome weapons that each have their own unique playstyle. Daggers, broadswards, longswords, rapiers, spears, flails, whips, bows, crossbows, cat'o nine tails, a blunderbuss, so much awesomeness. Plus there are different types of weapons too, iron, gold, blood, glass, titanium, and obsidian, each with thier own perks.Many types of armour so you can take more punishment. Leather, chainmail, plate, obsidion, glass, heavy plate, and more.Your shovel allows you to dig up certain types of blocks where you can find rooms full of enemies, or a hidden chest, or even keys to special chests.Different types of boots give you the ability to ignore certain types of traps, terrain, or other various things, each helping out in it's own way.On your head you can equip a crown of teleportation, circlet of telekenises so you can see enemies and the contents of chests, or a helmet to increase your armour more.Torches help you spot monsters in the darkness or secrets in the walls. Magical torches shed light on everything so even well hidden secrets become yours.SOOOO many monsters!!! Each with unique movements and attack patterns, then on top of that different versions of each monster that get harder each level.In the end, get this game, it's in alpha and it plays like it could be a standalone. I rarely run into glitches or problems and I play this game alot. If you like rogue-likes at all, this is one that will make the top of your list. Revolutionary in so many ways just like ToME and other new rogue-likes."
,Recommended,247080,12852436,"Posted: 8 November, 2014",all,whiteinge,"A smart and challenging roguelike that keeps your toe tapping to the beat. There's very little bad about this game, the enemies are varied and interesting, the bosses are tough, the weapons are varied and interesting, the buffs are varied and interesting. Some of the hard-core challenges are insane. It is perfectly playable as-is but could benefit from a little polish going forward -- more gentile level transitions, and it is tough to play with a gamepad since items are triggered with the directional keys.The game is tough as nails but the unlocks for upgrades / drops keep a sense of progression. The unlockable practice rooms are genius. And dying is never that big a deal since the music is so fun to play to.If you like rhythm games and don't have much experience with roguelikes, you will find an excellent rhythm game that keeps you mentally engaged as you stay a few beats ahead of the action to position yourself to survive. (And it wouldn't hurt to read a minor spoiler or two to get a leg-up on the roguelike discoverability game mechanics.)If you like roguelikes and don't have much experience with rhythm games, you will find a top-notch roguelike that requires attention to detail, offers plenty of discoverability, and has deep and challenging game mechanics -- all set to a fantastic beat.If you like rhythm games and roguelikes there is absolutely zero reason to not pick this up immediately. And maybe also remember to send the developer a valentine next Feb. 14th."
