,Recommended,247080,15690190,"Posted: 4 May, 2015",all,Wormerine,"It's solid. Entertaining in short bursts. Played it for quite a bit and probably will play some more. I am a bit disappointed with it though.You see, it describes itself as a roguelike rhythm game. There isn't much rhythm in there. Now, the problem might be, that I am a classicaly trained musician and the way I see rhythm is probably a bit different. My issues might not be revelant to other players.How I would describe this game is a roguelike with simple mechanics but with a quite clever gimmick. Turns happen on their own in regular intervals, not when you move (as in classic rogue-likes). Enemies move in certain patterns (some move every turn, other every other turn etc.) The tricky part is to quickly evaluate your enemies and make right decisions in a short time given. To help you move in the right time turns are sincronized with music. That is really all there is to it. Also, the game is very forgiving when it comes to moving on time.Occasionally, things get a bit more interesting. There are traps, which accelerate/slow down turns (and music.) There is one boss fight, where rhythm is irregular (one beat is skipped.) There is one miniboss, which disables the music until you kill it (never found it to be an issue... everyone can just tap a perfectly even rhythm, right?)There are some choices in the design, which I am still not sure whenever I like or not. Do do have a choice of different characters but rather than offering alternative playstyles, they give you special challenges. I thought it to be a strange choice but I do like it more and more. The game core-mechanics are too basic to allow for different ""playstyles"" so just complicating things by creating special rules for all of the characters is a welcome addition. The weapons are very very unbalanced. However, the good ones seem to be difficult to get in the actual run. It work alright in the end.Not a too big a fan of the soundtrack. I am usually a big fan of Danny B soundtracks, but this one is a bit dull. Probably the issue is the big focus on a regular beat, which I find to be snooze worthy. Comeon, rhythm is an importan part of music. You cant be THAT regular.So lots of negative things. But it is still fun. Give it a bash. Probably none of my issues will be relevant to you."
