76561198046617310,Recommended,247080,16031507,"Posted: 27 May, 2015",all,FroggyIntention,"I'd been itching to play this throughout the Early Access, but just because of that, I waited till the release so I would be even more impressed. And heck, I was impressed. The more I play Crypt of the Necrodancer, the more things I find to appreciate. Ultimately simple using only four keys to play the game, but with a good amount of items, monsters, songs, bosses and characters to suit your disco of a dungeon crawl to make it both challenging and leave plenty to try as I continue exploring the crypt. Danny B's soundtrack is wonderful, it's fitting and mighty fine to slay monsters to, with the alternative soundtracks and the custom track option, even more opportunities open up. Monsters are both terrifying and downright adorable with their individual dances, and the bosses are simple in theory but perform so well. The inclusion of a daily challenge is entertaining and feeds the desire for so many players to just keep going, and something I was very glad to see included. I've noticed a few comments about the levels being timed, since when the beat drops, your heart stops. Personally I feel fine with this, not only do I feel the songs give you about the right time to explore everything, but it helps keep a pressure on your back that I would far rather have than not in keeping the drive of the crawl. It's not the Binding of Isaac, sure, but I don't want it to be. Absolutely I recommend this game as long as players jive and zombies thrive."
