76561198094678213,Recommended,247080,16216058,"Posted: 5 June, 2015",all,bigM30W,"If you like randomized dungeon crawlers, this game is for you... if you have the patience for it.This game breathes a breath of fresh air into the dungeon crawler genre with its interesting twist of having to move and attack to the beat of the music. The wide array of characters, weapons, items, and powerups gives this game plenty of replay value. I personally love this game and would recommend it but beware, it's not for everyone.Pros: -Awesome soundtrack and appealing graphics (if you like 8-bit graphics)-Replay value out of the roof-Steam workshop compatibility which adds even more new things to play with!Cons: -having to wait to move (except for the bard character)-Can get a little monotonousRating? 9.75 out of 10"
76561198096968619,Recommended,247080,16151557,"Posted: 3 June, 2015",all,Fiery Kitsune,"GameplayThis game takes the traditional top-down roguelike and puts a simple however game-changing spin on it: Moving only at the beat of the music.Except for the Bard. Then the movement time limit is lifted. This adds a bit of a turn-based stratergy to it, with the enemies having very predictable patterns (except the bats. I hateallof them), it gives you the ability to plan your attack so long as you can plan it in under a second. Remember: you move at the beat of the music. If you are thinking that this is simple enough, WRONG! This game is fffffffffffffffffHARD! Throughout the game - especially in the later dungeons - you are fighting off hordes of monsters so you have to take a lot into consideration: the range of one monster, the movement patterns of another, the traps laid around the room and the attack patterns of your weapons, which flows perfectly into the next subject.WeaponsThe weapons in this game are greatly varied, however I dare say biased because I see some a LOT more often than others. With each weapon having its own attack pattern, everybody has the ability to choose their own favourite weapon. Do you like having extra space on theene,my?Go with the spear. Like to deal bous damage? Go with the rapier. Want to attack everything around you? Choose the cat of nine tails. Along side the vast array of weapons you can find comes the modifiers to the weapons where you can deal extra damage once certain conditions are met. However these modifiers are harder to find and once you do find them, they cost a bit more if they are being sold.MusicThe music is awesome and catchy and I bet at one point you will be tapping your foot to the beat of the music as you make your way through the levels. What adds to the music and makes it stand apart from any other games' OST is that the item merchant sings along so long as you are close enough to hear him. Also interesting isthe music changes styles as you replay the game with either Melody or Aria.tl;drAll in all, this game is hard but awesome. Buy it.Edit: I forgot to mention as I was writing this, expect many cheap deaths in the game unless your brain is a supercomputer. Especially when you are approaching the end. The weapons don't seem to help much as you can get stuck in one spot attacking something until it - or more likely you - dies when you actually meant to retreat. The only way to avoid this is if you get your hands on the Ring of Courage or a Rapier. This flaw is a pretty big one however the game is still incredible."
