,Recommended,247080,12813474,"Posted: 6 November, 2014",all,CrankShade,"Love this game, it's addicting!First off what the game is about. It's a procedurally generated rogue-like, where you're this girl looking for her dad (according to the trailer anyways, but is not mentioned in the game). You navigate on a grid tile floor and all your moves can ONLY BE MADE TO THE BEAT OF THE MUSIC indicated by the moving bars at the bottom of the screen. And that's what makes the game. You play through ""zones"" which each are a different set of enemies, traps, and rewards. Each Zone has 3 floors and a boss floor. You can dig through weak enough walls and must kill monsters on the way to the stairs, use the earned gold to buy better equipment. Theoretically you can play through the whole game untouched from damage, as you can predict the movements of the enemies. However, the tempo of the game pressures you to keep moving with the beat and maintaining your timing which may cause you to make a wrong move. If you're off beat, or you prematurely try to move, you miss the beat and won't move. This also resets your gold multiplier, and the enemies will make their move anyways.My favorite thing about this game is all this combined with kickass music. That's what makes it so addicting.Definitely play with a controller tho. Playing with the keyboard made my wrist hurt real quick. I play with the WASD keys (who moves with arrow keys?) and the rhythmic repetition quickly hurts your wrist in a short time.That aside, this is one of the most unique games I have ever played. The developers did a fantastic job with it so far. 99% positive reviews!For good reasons.If I had to criticize the game in ANY way, it would be the menu navigating. It's confusing until you realize (for some reason) left is to go back and right is to confirm selection, and the start button is not to resume the game but also a confirm selection button.I highly recommend this game. A must have!"
76561198028131682,Recommended,247080,13112434,"Posted: 27 November, 2014",all,zAppi,"If you love both music and games at the same time as much as I do, you will be thrilled by how amazing it is once you'll try it out!The roguelike mechanic itself is not so special, you run around the dungeons, die, buy some permanent upgrades, go back, die, go back, etc. But what makes it really stand out is the music and rhytm mechanic that glues EVERYTHING together. Even writing this post I'm feeling like I have to press the keys in a right way not to lose coins multiplier...Seriously, this game, even in alpha, is absolutely worth it!"
