76561198053526912,Recommended,247080,13100612,"Posted: 26 November, 2014",all,Dimitrios1610,"At first when I found footage from this game, I had no idea what I was looking at. Watching a couple of videos was all it took for me to make the purchase and I am very glad I did.Crypt of the Necrodancer is a thoroughly enjoyable and ridiculous hybrid of a dungeon crawler and a rhythm game, where actions like moving, attacking, casting spells, and using items are all done to the beat of the music. The sprite animation style is incredibly charming, reminiscent of certain Super Nintendo titles with more fluid motion that make the game sing.The game's soundtrack bears special mention. Since music is so important in CotN, the music is upbeat, powerful techno and dance tunes that will get your head bobbing and your fingers flying. When using custom music, a very cool feature, there can be some weird inconsistencies in the beat the computer records and the actual music, but nothing tremendously off-putting.Currently there are three zones in the game and multiple characters (I only have access to two at the moment, counting the starting hero), which gives a good incentive to keep playing, acquiring items, and retrying dungeons with the new equipment trying to progress.For an Early Access game, Crypt is an incredibly polished, enjoyable experience. Fans of old-school games, rhythm games, and anyone who enjoys a good soundtrack should definitely buy in."
